Saudi British Jumps to Month High as Earnings Surge 91 Percent

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-07-13T10:24:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/saudi-british-jumps-to-month-high-as-earnings-surge-91-percent.html
Saudi British Bank (SABB)  rallied to the
highest level in more than a month after the lender that’s 40
percent owned by HSBC Holdings Plc said second-quarter profit
soared 91 percent, beating analysts’ estimates.  The shares increased 4.3 percent to 43.2 riyals, the
highest intraday level since June 8, at 12:32 p.m. in  Riyadh .  Net income for the quarter rose to 852 million riyals ($227
million) from 447 million riyals a year earlier. The mean
estimate of seven analysts was for a profit of 669.9 million
riyals, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
